= Kill Camera Motion Blur =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Removes time samples from camera primitives to disable camera motion blur."""

== Overview ==

Kill Camera Motion Blur strips all time samples from camera transform and property attributes, collapsing them to a single static value at the current frame. This effectively disables camera motion blur for the affected cameras while leaving object motion blur on other primitives untouched.

This node has no parameters. Connect it after the camera in the LOP network.
